{
  "texts": [
    "The unified encoder in 5c is transformed from the text encoder by adding audio tokens to the existing text token vocabulary.",
    "Light Audio Encoder refers to a lightweight encoder used behind a CTC alignment layer.",
    "Whisper-Large-v2 Encoder without a 30-second padding limit.3 Configurable Encoder includes Whisper, WavLM, and HuBERT.",
    "Configurable Projector includes Linear + ReLU + Linear, and Q-Former.",
    "Configurable LLM includes Vicuna-7B, etc.4 Details about specific pretrained models are not publicly disclosed.5 Certain components are not detailed in the paper; presumed to be standard linear downsampling or Transformer-based adapters.6 The encoder of Kimi-Audio combines discrete semantic tokens and continuous whisper features, making it a hybrid model that does not strictly follow continuous sequence modeling for Speech LLMs."
  ]
}